 solving, and makes the case for a renewed embrace of human ingenuity that is particularly important today. Her lucid and engaging prose is illustrated with a wealth of rare and extraordinary images showing the history of the medium, from hand-drawn diagrams and close-ups of pre-Columbian textiles to material studies with corn, paper, and the typewriter, as well as illuminating examples of her own work.Now available for a new generation of readers, this expanded edition of On Weaving updates the book's original black-and-white illustrations with full-color photos, and features an afterword by Nicholas Fox Weber and essays by Manuel Cirauqui and T'ai Smith that shed critical light on Albers and her career.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArtxTechniquesxGeneral. 7aART / Individual Artists / General.2bisacsh1 aCirauqui, Manuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCirauqui, Manuel.1 aSmith, T`ai.1 aSmith, T'Ai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeber, Nicholas Fox, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeber, Nicholas Fox.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311054332240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400889044zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400889044423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400889044.jpg  a978-3-11-054332-2  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK